1 c. An elderly adult who has disappeared, whose disappearance has been reported
2 to law enforcement and the disappearance:
3 (1) May pose an imminent risk of personal injury to the adult or others, as
4 determined by a law enforcement agency based on a report received from
5 the missing adult's family member which contains sufficient evidence of the
6 imminent risk;
7 (2) Poses a threat to the health and safety of the adult due to the environment
8 or severe winter, cold, or windy weather conditions, as determined by a law
9 enforcement agency based on a report received from the missing adult's
10 family member which contains sufficient evidence of the threat to health or
11 safety; or
12 (3) Warrants a silver alert notice activation due to the particular circumstances
13 or duration of the disappearance, as determined by a law enforcement
14 agency based on a report received from the missing adult's family member
15 which contains sufficient evidence that the particular circumstances or
16 duration warrant a silver alert notice activation.
17 4. "Silver alert notice" means an urgent bulletin using the emergency alert system to air a
18 description of a missing individual to aid in the location of that individual.
19 Alert notice system activation.
20 1. A law enforcement agency may request the bureau of criminal investigation or the
21 superintendent of the highway patrol to activate an amber alert notice, a blue alert
22 notice, or a silver alert notice.
23 2. The bureau of criminal investigation, in cooperation with the highway patrol, shall
24 prepare an operational plan to prepare for and respond to requests for activation of an
25 amber alert notice, a blue alert notice, or a silver alert notice. The plan must include
26 the role and requirements of the division of state radio of the department of emergency
27 services in broadcasting an alert to the public.
28 Minimum requirements for activating an amber or blue alert notice.
29 1. An amber alert notice may not be activated unless:
30 a. The abduction involves a child seventeen years of age or younger;
